            </h2>
            <p class="cs-text">
                Agentlist was founded in early 2024 by Ali after she experienced
                firsthand how difficult it can be to find the right real estate
                agent after leaving the Army. Before jumping into the real
                estate world, Ali spent six years as an Army Aircraft Commander
                flying MQ-1C Grey Eagles. She logged nearly 1,500 flight hours
                and was awarded a Purple Heart following a missile attack during
                her deployment to Iraq. When she decided to finish her
                enlistment to focus on raising her family, she realized the
                transition to finding a home wasn't as seamless as it should be
                for service members. Because of it, she decided to take matters
                into her own hands. Ali started the company while pregnant and
                today, she runs the business as a mom of two. Agentlist's
                mission is to make sure soldiers are taken care of by agents who
